[recv] {"type": "turn_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Exploring classloader options**\n\nI'm thinking about the custom classloader — the first call should return a Package if one is defined, but I can't have inconsistencies. I’m considering using something like PackageDefinitionStrategy to return the defined package for the default package. It seems like a possible solution, but I want to make sure it works reliably. There’s definitely some complexity here that I need to navigate carefully to avoid potential issues later on.\n\n**Evaluating error handling in tests**\n\nI’m considering whether the native run test should catch errors or exceptions. It seems like ClassInjector UsingReflection could be false if injection fails, which may lead to an IllegalStateException when init returns Unavailable. Should I focus on handling errors only, not exceptions? I wonder if the rule should only catch errors related to unsupported dynamic class loading. It’s a bit tricky! I’ll have to clarify how best to manage these situations.\n\n**Investigating dynamic loading errors**\n\nI need to look into NativeImageSupport and try to understand if it’s failing for other reasons beyond just the Error itself. It seems that dynamic class loading often triggers UnsupportedFeatureError. There's a chance ClassInjector might detect Graal issues and then lead to an Unavailable state. If that happens, it's possible that injecting raw dispatcher methods could throw an IllegalStateException. I should inspect the Unavailable error next.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_016c67c62a44ff910169f8054c29cc81918fe198e3edfe3ae9\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-AVj0vGMT2eco9GZrsVKdgty0W9b821Cwh9cNB1v4ofLZNfICYbsMLFU2-TApPpS6QcdrolWryAqjGwzVVJKEUi1oMPKCtftz_piwjy5Fg5W-xVOE1nS937WniEih--_4CkG_ybD9MDLi9TjlJXm2jdWPTZ6v99tFiL1r-GYFEY_X0AsHLQRH5ORpP5TP-4n1SIGsZSO4ZcGeLF3t8-t2PhelQzoQTRaUBfBf3nVwGynzCN6G6hpBXrLhP_thcW-AgAZclWaKy2aX39