[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering test coverage**\n\nI’m thinking about keeping coverage for each dynamic-access class in its own dedicated Java test file. I wonder if having a placeholder violates any guidelines. Should I remove the placeholder? It might just be a scaffold-only piece. The new library test review catches scaffold-only parts, but that’s not applicable here since it’s not new. So, I’m debating whether I could remove the placeholder or change it to something more meaningful.\n\n**Considering error handling**\n\nI'm thinking about how to catch the IllegalStateException. I want to check the cause for errors related to NativeImageSupport, which might indicate if unsupported features are the problem. It seems consistent to verify this with NativeImageSupport—after all, the error is wrapped. Maybe I could implement a helper to rethrow unexpected errors. I'm also considering whether to catch RuntimeException and if that might be related to library detection.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_016c67c62a44ff910169f805a755748191be607e84f2a99ada\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-AW2VpeWl1bRUUJgRCB-CrDbZxsm1FT7zRgSH6ljqXiPAK40__nX74HEUYOSvNNh6uW8UKR3kxWcTTtE-otdzOq1Yy4xvw6tSrz5bfCe6cSwlFp8bmrntLty249TAmMDxIW-wD_JqwPfMnyPcsa9bHTVoJ9G6b5M4xn3s4pU_E-PUKYCsyMuTwepwiugWaLMLpgggARVDU8tLan2MaKNYiv4OWorrvFKhBFaB9gUvJufZT-WPh4WgQ-kzkt1wOIwO9KlvaIy-MKybOpEnY7a-6lRye5PHJJKyUWA_UMQB5br9s3b2NwOR3nejNKR3i9oWc2b0nQmb9GDwluRWsP_TYsk8EE042B7cjUZwY_Tvj6F60X46xSllMWaSDvbZqz-ZpSSsi-2wKW_FFx8WOCI2hGQXQrcAYAYxjMs-7zUwsy7ts7fpadge6dXI4fF5K3RohQ5PJwVPFQDpiPtZCIVxK8tYuUbAJuX9KnuT39Uj9uC6yc9DvjYgdkVeIFl7SXlUe3KPcOltxsd5OQORRXe1ooSZaxSoOpHcuCnrPihusyvP75kpJQgPalaV4z7RiUzHsN-lazKn2wzxlJtrWJCsFI5Xb-Xo7s8DOZ9wq515vtjFklVrhs9rmVA1I-9-0nbd4L9jZmkJEk6NlQo6igqF2jtT0OUjPKUiWKadMMc8FBfm5aN42-SVzbFdFBlPhslTGfcTReraC1JSBo54DrMEZfkuk095L17mncJo1_JsPIN_F24tua_KT6s5Xj5autnwPO89ow82DCRKQWw