[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Evaluating method accessibility**\n\nI’m thinking about whether the static method can call `make()`. Yes, a protected static method can be accessed inside a subclass, but I wonder if this violates the principle of not using direct reflection. The test seems to be about accessing the public/protected API via the subclass, rather than using Java reflection. If we keep tests outside the library package, it might be fine to force `make()` actively irrespective of `UsingUnsafe.isAvailable`.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_016c67c62a44ff910169f80745aa148191952f8a2ed7be8e40\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp-AdQEFtpGwREZurwtcPugKKDb4Q-YrSRjsFCsDoIM-IHL9fjPw3_laSvhjs3aaiSIwRaEJ_ZIqQSMUFYNrXHnGsjo-fme-Qqkl5WJc2cZYWiJytIg3gmIp6jGG-0D3li8VZLLVJMmap9oYXHTLU7pXROVI7ZZS1IKA4050vmdA_BXnVP_4SEWE9uF2EhsJyz-36quXOMEfjYIzIIDglgZEPjubHWW7JmrJUcoq39s7S9dtYqi5t9w5OIenvq8SVrRAaa7DqNoISM-VrlsPF4wGtfIXQzU15qcU7Fyyi_KJvN1PYrSRGR2lb08KOqYLkBy0nGae5vmnKreBVhAk-ZawBLg-eTZ2SutR9SZtlSRWLtZOvKDvZ-EmgoyPSJ3PzmoOO7L6F7RSe4StjPFwUvBPwLO4SbaPE5Hl0D72bMtXYpaEJ-DWhE4BffuZrKeRWdISlJJbmcV48pBstH9OjNtB6BS2ts66YoC5P8SeJhaU2UwXCsSVpMDIcnNTCJRJhjoRKuVL8r5BOcKeJwtWM_cuhJYkUC4sWkramFh63gBMhCtH_QKirRgYbg2Q46Ed7FZKyOUafwJS6_83ldA2E8Tvfvy_gQroG-T67cxXcBTv9wepL5__O9vuBxoiO-zcjG5zuAnlRCDxjH7O9ZZ9286HYxDMzH52NYRSGKG5pEAmsBy3Ci7de9e29Cce4re2KWlvRXOKBBchYrZbCgDXmBDRbbwuzgSoINtWVTGs3rSoWoS4oj8wbSrlyXoufh7IcfgXrtyqOI0tMdlIyu8Vakir20xo8y6eAg1DQVlsGF-MeHwy2rQQlpLZCmUxQOFwy83rWeeXce3FWFY03VSIjWULLvz8PINeN7K-brgS274Gy5y6QoPUm3yf5WZEelKMRO2bZqTvDwFV0B5-xwH8oDGCBj0jUuCUsqpd8rSaNJwmKfN5DDZ9KPe4GP-Xsh6CimZ4S-hsSGiH_9wHx5UlU35uv08cfRG3_xV_wjh8zn-frjmAZmQZH7aEGjj2Zh04M3B10883ISz1oZOamlrkflO00wqIwIyGExL4v6MSlHNtlhI2deZNak3nrVb5kacSwkn7wzdj4G1qgkKa3POF31ljejHeTij7hQao9Iv2Hu-yHkmAgRakzHIutJfMFys9txtt-lZioHdbkuuZNf3WuALgZ4DkRqwBqOv2HsHa7AvWwJdgpFItETnccmeteNsdY-KeAD4wK0EaWUVLP3yOURjWOrVGwntUgvuBIY