rror of `AccessibleObject` using a ByteBuddy wrapper to access the overridden field from that mirror. I wonder how this affects performance and accessibility within Java applications. It seems like a nuanced area!\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing reachability metadata**\\n\\nI’m considering changing the reachability metadata to make something native, but it seems there's no coverage. Perhaps we need to focus on branch coverage under the JVM instead of JDK25, since the TCK is using JDK25. It looks like having an active class might be impossible on JDK25. However, a dynamic-access report suggests that the active class was analyzed differently, showing uncovered call sites and implying the class might be loaded by a native agent. But it wasn’t covered because the test didn’t hit it.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Assessing error handling**\\n\\nI'm considering rules specific to error handling. It seems like an existing native method might fail, which could lead to a RuntimeException if there’s an unsupported feature. I’ve already created a helper for this, so I think I can use the same wrapper approach. In JVM, it should successfully pass, while the native might need to catch the exception separately. This leads me to think about implementing a common helper method wrapper more effectively. Time to edit!\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_lBh4oTh72wDbYC7EGkMRKNSi|fc_016c67c62a44ff910169f80850c7f08191bdf69a509e82862d", "name": "edit", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeInjectionTest.java", "edits": [{"oldText": "import java.net.URL;\nimport java.security.Permission;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.Map;\n", "newText": "import java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.net.URL;\nimport java.security.Permission;\nimport java.security.ProtectionDomain;\nimport java.util.Collections;\nimport java.util.Map;\n"}, {"oldText": "    @Test\n    void reflectionInjectorUsesUnsafeAccessorForClassAndPackageOperations() {\n", "newText": "    @Test\n    void unsafeInjectionDispatcherInvokesAccessorMethods() {\n        try {\n            UnsafeInjectionHarness.exerciseDispatcherMethods();\n        } catch (Error error) {\n            if (!NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(error)) {\n                throw error;\n            }\n        } catch (RuntimeException exception) {\n            if (!isCausedByUnsupportedFeatureError(exception)) {\n                throw exception;\n            }\n        } catch (Exception exception) {\n            throw new IllegalStateException(exception);\n        }\n    }\n\n    @Test\n    void reflectionInjectorUsesUnsafeAccessorForClassAndPackageOperations() {\n"}, {"oldText": "    private static final class PermissiveSecurityManager extends SecurityManager {\n        @Override\n        public void checkPermission(Permission permission) {\n        }\n    }\n}\n", "newText": "    private static final class UnsafeInjectionHarness extends ClassInjector.UsingReflection {\n        private UnsafeInjectionHarness(ClassLoader classLoader) {\n            super(classLoader);\n        }\n\n        private static void exerciseDispatcherMethods() throws Exception {\n            Accessor accessor = new Accessor();\n            Dispatcher dispatcher = new HarnessDispatcher(\n                    accessor,\n                    accessorMethod(\"findLoadedClass\", ClassLoader.class, String.class),\n                    accessorMethod(\"defineClass\", ClassLoader.class, String.class, byte[].class,\n                            int.class, int.class, ProtectionDomain.class),\n                    accessorMethod(\"getDefinedPackage\", ClassLoader.class, String.class),\n                    accessorMethod(\"getPackage\", ClassLoader.class, String.class),\n                    accessorMethod(\"definePackage\", ClassLoader.class, String.class, String.class,\n                            String.class, String.class, String.class, String.class, String.class, URL.class),\n                    accessorMethod(\"getClassLoadingLock\", ClassLoader.class, String.class)\n            ).initialize();\n\n            DispatcherClassLoader classLoader = new DispatcherClassLoader(\n                    ClassInjectorInnerUsingReflectionInnerDispatcherInnerUsingUnsafeInjectionTest.class\n                            .getClassLoader());\n            String packageName = PACKAGE_PREFIX + \"dispatcher\" + Long.toUnsignedString(System.nanoTime());\n            String className = packageName + \".Injected\";\n            byte[] classFile = new ByteBuddy()\n                    .subclass(Object.class)\n                    .name(className)\n                    .make()\n                    .getBytes();\n\n            assertThat(dispatcher.getClassLoadingLock(classLoader, className)).isSameAs(classLoader);\n            assertThat(dispatcher.findClass(classLoader, className)).isNull();\n            assertThat(dispatcher.getDefinedPackage(classLoader, packageName)).isNull();\n\n            Package definedPackage = dispatcher.definePackage(\n                    classLoader, packageName, null, null, null, null, null, null, null);\n            assertThat(definedPackage.getName()).isEqualTo(packageName);\n            assertThat(dispatcher.getDefinedPackage(classLoader, packageName)).isSameAs(definedPackage);\n            assertThat(dispatcher.getPackage(classLoader, packageName)).isSameAs(definedPackage);\n\n            Class<?> definedClass = dispatcher.defineClass(classLoader, className, classFile, null);\n            assertThat(definedClass.getName()).isEqualTo(className);\n            assertThat(definedClass.getClassLoader()).isSameAs(classLoader);\n            assertThat(dispatcher.findClass(classLoader, className)).isSameAs(definedClass);\n        }\n\n        private static Method accessorMethod(String name, Class<?>... parameterTypes) throws NoSuchMethodException {\n            return Accessor.class.getMethod(name, parameterTypes);\n        }\n\n        private static final class HarnessDispatcher extends Dispatcher.UsingUnsafeInjection {\n            private HarnessDispatcher(Object accessor, Method findLoadedClass, Method defineClass,\n                    Method getDefinedPackage, Method getPackage, Method definePackage,\n                    Method getClassLoadingLock) {\n                super(accessor, findLoadedClass, defineClass, getDefinedPackage, getPackage,\n                        definePackage, getClassLoadingLock);\n            }\n        }\n    }\n\n    public static final class Accessor {\n        public Object getClassLoadingLock(ClassLoader classLoader, String name) {\n            return classLoader;\n        }\n\n        public Class<?> findLoadedClass(ClassLoader classLoader, String name) {\n            try {\n                return Class.forName(name, false, classLoader);\n            } catch (ClassNotFoundException exception) {\n                return null;\n            }\n        }\n\n        public Class<?> defineClass(ClassLoader classLoader, String name, byte[] binaryRepresentation,\n                int offset, int length, ProtectionDomain protectionDomain) {\n            return ((DispatcherClassLoader) classLoader)\n                    .defineClassForTest(name, binaryRepresentation, offset, length, protectionDomain);\n        }\n\n        public Package getDefinedPackage(ClassLoader classLoader, String name) {\n            return ((DispatcherClassLoader) classLoader).getDefinedPackageForTest(name);\n        }\n\n        public Package getPackage(ClassLoader classLoader, String name) {\n            return ((DispatcherClassLoader) classLoader).getPackageForTest(name);\n        }\n\n        public Package definePackage(ClassLoader classLoader, String name, String specificationTitle,\n                String specificationVersion, String specificationVendor, String implementationTitle,\n                String implementationVersion, String implementationVendor, URL sealBase) {\n            return ((DispatcherClassLoader) classLoader).definePackageForTest(\n                    name,\n                    specificationTitle,\n                    specificationVersion,\n                    specificationVendor,\n                    implementationTitle,\n                    implementationVersion,\n                    implementationVendor,\n                    sealBase);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class DispatcherClassLoader extends ClassLoader {\n        private DispatcherClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n            super(parent);\n        }\n\n        private Class<?> defineClassForTest(String name, byte[] binaryRepresentation, int offset,\n                int length, ProtectionDomain protectionDomain) {\n            return defineClass(name, binaryRepresentation, offset, length, protectionDomain);\n        }\n\n        private Package definePackageForTest(String name, String specificationTitle,\n                String specificationVersion, String specificationVendor, String implementationTitle,\n                String implementationVersion, String implementationVendor, URL sealBase) {\n            return definePackage(name, specificationTitle, specificationVersion, specificationVendor,\n                    implementationTitle, implementationVersion, implementationVendor, sealBase);\n        }\n\n        private Package getDefinedPackageForTest(String name) {\n            return getDefinedPackage(name);\n        }\n\n        private Package getPackageForTest(String name) {\n            return getPackage(name);\n        }\n    }\n\n    private static final class PermissiveSecurityManager extends SecurityManager {\n        @Override\n        public void checkPermission(Permission permission) {\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}]}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 6761, "o